## 10. Conditional Rendering (Frontend)

```
// Boolean toggle: use && (short-circuit)
{canEdit && <EditButton onClick={handleEdit} />}

// Two states: use ternary
{isLoading ? <Skeleton /> : <Content data={data} />}

// Multiple states: use early return or switch-like pattern
if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />;
if (error) return <ErrorState onRetry={refetch} />;
if (!data.length) return <EmptyState hint="No records found" />;
return <ResourceList items={data} />;
```

### Rules

- **`&&` for show/hide** - but ONLY with booleans (never `{count && <Badge />}` - 0 renders as "0")
- **Always ternary for two states** - never use if/else when ternary works. Avoid nesting beyond 2 levels.
- **Early return for multiple states** - loading -> error -> empty -> content (always in this sequence)
- **Never hide with CSS when you can not-render** - unmounted components don't waste resources
- **Complex conditions** get extracted to a variable:
  ```
  BANNED:  {user && user.role === "admin" && permissions.includes("edit") && <EditButton />}
  REQUIRED: const canShowEditButton = user?.role === "admin" && permissions.includes("edit");
            {canShowEditButton && <EditButton />}
  ```

