## 11. Data Transformation Pattern

When transforming data between layers (API -> UI, DB -> API), always use explicit mapping functions:

```
// Map DB model to API response (always expose "id", never raw "_id" or internal keys)
function toResourceResponse(record) {
  return {
    id: (record._id ?? record.id).toString(),
    title: record.title,
    email: record.email,
    category: record.category?.name ?? null,
    status: record.isActive ? "active" : "inactive",
    createdAt: record.createdAt.toISOString(),
  };
}

// Map API response to UI display
function toResourceDisplay(apiRecord) {
  return {
    ...apiRecord,
    initials: getInitials(apiRecord.title),
    statusColor: apiRecord.status === "active" ? "green" : "gray",
    createdFormatted: formatRelativeDate(apiRecord.createdAt),
  };
}
```

### Rules

- **Explicit mapping functions** - never pass raw DB objects to the API response or raw API responses to the UI
- **Name the mapping function** - `toXxxResponse`, `toXxxDisplay`, `fromXxxRequest`
- **Map at the boundary** - at the edge of each layer, not deep inside
- **No spread-and-pray** - don't `{ ...dbRecord }` as the response (leaks internal fields)

